threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib/ld-uClibc.so.0, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This MIPS32 ELF binary is a highly functional DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt. It features robust persistence mechanisms, competition-killing capabilities, and diverse attack vectors. Key behaviors include establishing persistence by modifying '/etc/rc.local' and creating init scripts (e.g., '/etc/init.d/sysd'), hiding its process presence by spoofing process names and PIDs, and implementing a 'killer' module that scans '/proc/net/tcp' and '/proc' to terminate competing malicious processes. The sample contains numerous DDoS attack functions (attack_app_http, attack_udpflood, attack_icmpflood, etc.) and communicates with a Command & Control (C2) server to receive instructions. Notable IOCs include the use of '/tmp/.instance_lock', persistence scripts at '/usr/bin/.sh', and the targeting of system startup files.
